comments: I agree that vaccines are necessary. I disagree over the increasing number of vaccines being produced by the pharmaceutical companies. I especially disagree with the state governments that are making some of these obtuse vaccines a requirement for school aged children. In PA, the chicken pox vaccine and the booster shot were required by state law when my daughter was school age. Like a good parent, I made sure she had her shots. She was 16 when she received the booster shot. After that she kept getting more and more run down, taking naps after school. She began missing days of school, scheduling the "sick" days so she could still participate in her school activities such as Concert Choir. Five months after receiving the booster shot, she literally could not get out of bed for three weeks. Eventually she was diagnosed with ME/CFS and spent the next 5 years housebound and isolated as she dealt with the pain and symptoms associated with ME/CFS. She has recovered to about 50% of her pre-illness health and energy level.  Each day she has to be careful about so many things so that she does not get thrown into PEM or a flare-up. This is her life. Guess what?  PA no longer requires the chicken pox shot.  Isn't that interesting?
